rl":"/avatars/telemachus-100.png","invited_by_user":"jcs"},"tags":["practices","programming","python"]},{"short_id":"m0hy9r","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/m0hy9r","created_at":"2022-06-18T14:41:41.000-05:00","title":"What’s the state of IDLs for JSON API?","url":"","score":6,"flags":0,"comment_count":22,"description":"\u003cp\u003eLet’s say I am writing a small thing, and I want to expose it as a simple JSON rpc. I value simplicity, so grpc and (I think) graphql are out.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf I want to define the API via language independent IDL, what are my choices? I know that JSON schema exists, but it doesn’t seem like a good IDL (not human readable, too much non-type based validation built-in, haven’t seen it actually being used in real world).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI kinda like the style LSP is defined in, via a bunch of TS interfaces, but that’s an informal subset.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAnything else to take a look at?\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"Let’s say I am writing a small thing, and I want to expose it as a simple JSON rpc. I value simplicity, so grpc and (I think) graphql are out.\r\n\r\nIf I want to define the API via language independent IDL, what are my choices? I know that JSON schema exists, but it doesn’t seem like a good IDL (not human readable, too much non-type based validation built-in, haven’t seen it actually being used in real world).\r\n\r\nI kinda like the style LSP is defined in, via a bunch of TS interfaces, but that’s an informal subset.\r\n\r\nAnything else to take a look at?","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/m0hy9r/what_s_state_idls_for_json_api","submitter_user":{"username":"matklad","created_at":"2019-07-02T07:23:10.000-05:00","is_admin":false,"about":"Working on IDE support for the Rust language.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/matklad","is_moderator":false,"karma":2966,"avatar_url":"/avatars/matklad-100.png","invited_by_user":"skade","github_username":"matklad"},"tags":["api","ask"]},{"short_id":